  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "LORRY DRIVER",
  "description": "<ul><li>Operating and driving a lorry to transport goods and materials over specified routes to local or distant points according to a time schedule</li><li>Inspecting vehicles for mechanical items and safety issues and perform preventative maintenance</li><li>Complying with lorry driving rules and regulations (size, weight, route designations, parking and break periods) as well as with company policies and procedures</li><li>Planning routes and meeting delivery schedules</li><li>Loading and unloading cargo from the lorry, often with the help of a forklift or other machinery</li><li>Collecting and verifying delivery instructions, including signatures from customers</li><li>Reporting defects, accidents or violations</li><li>Maintaining a logbook of their driving activities to ensure compliance with federal regulations governing the rest and work periods for operators</li><li>Keeping the lorry and associated equipment clean and in good working order</li><li>Communicating effectively with clients or dispatchers about delays or problems on the route</li></ul>",
